General:
- Always use pnpm when installing packages, running scripts, etc.
- Replace npm commands with pnpm commands.
- Do not edit the package.json file for package management directly, prefer using the pnpm CLI.

Commands:
- "build" - To build the project. Skips TypeScript checks and linting rules for faster builders.
- "dev" - To run the development server.
- "format" - To format code using Prettier.
- "lint" - To run ESLint linting rules.
- "start" - To start the server.
- "check" - To check for TypeScript errors and run ESLint linting rules.
- "stripe:listen" - To forward stripe webhook events.
- "sanity:typegen" - To genenerate types for @/sanity/types.
- "sanity:bridge" - To bridge the project with the Sanity Dashboard.